  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Marawi Crisis Emergency Response - SLR part 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- The new grant will be used to restart the livelihoods of IDPs that have returned to Marawi or those that are still staying ECs. This will use the SCLR approach.
 
-  Delivery of emergency response using survivor led response approach
-  capacity building among IDPs and ECOWEB staff on IDPs&apos; rights and advocacy
-  regular coordination meetings among CSOs and CBOs and with government and other agencies; rehabilitation planning</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- suffering of home based IDPs in 2 communities reduced through the SLR approach
- IDPs with CSOs are able to articulate and advocate their alternative rehabilitation plan for Marawi
- IDPs receive appropriate  and timely support from  Government, I/NGOs and IOs
- coordination and/orcollaboration among CSOs strengthened</narrative>
  </description>
